author: Undaunted Research

text:
As a newbie about to invest, you must have these three things in mind
1. Have a long term mindset.  
2. Be willing to take risk.
3. Be careful on money usage, if you're not spending to earn back, then stop spending.
4. Never claim to know - Ask questions and it's best you work with a financial advisor.  I made it as a newbie by working with Blaine Phillis jr, and today I can show alot of my achievements

author: Atul

text:
BUY more and offset your losses (for short term).¬†
Classic common man mentality is - you sell when it gets low, and buy when its high. No offence, but this is dumb mentality. However, true investors learn & understand the fundamentals of the instrument they invest in and then they "Buy more when the price falls, and sell (if necessary) when the price gets high".
author: Varun R

text:
Reg crypto - if you have invested in BTC and ETH, you can just HODL. 

Reg stocks - if you have invested in good stocks (definition: not overinflated, has good cash flows, can survive short term corrections), then hold on to them as well. 

If you have invested in bad stocks (definition: story stocks like paytm/zomato, overinflated stocks like few IT ones), sell them when the market goes on a bull run and reinvest that money in other good stocks. that's my advice based on what i learnt from Akshat. But as usual, pls do your due diligence as well and don't take others' advice on face value. üòÖ
